verse.lines:
{lang-eng}I Am So Glad That Our Father In Heaven
Tells Of His Love In The Book He Has Given;
Wonderful Things In The Bible I See,
This Is The Dearest, That Jesus Loves Me.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Though I Forget Him, And Wander Away,
Still He Doth Love Me Wherever I Stray;
Back To His Dear Loving Arms I Do Flee,
When I Remember That Jesus Loves Me.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Jesus Loves Me, And I Know I Love Him;
Love Brought Him Down My Poor Soul To Redeem;
Yes, It Was Love Made Him Die On The Tree;
Oh, I Am Certain That Jesus Loves Me!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}In This Assurance I Find Sweetest Rest,
Trusting In Jesus, I Know I Am Blessed;
Satan, Dismayed, From My Soul Now Doth Flee,
When I Just Tell Him That Jesus Loves Me.{/lang-eng}
